Brazil's new planning minister isAnibal Teixeira de Souza, the former head of a national welfareprogram, the government said.    Teixeira replaces economist Joao Sayad, who last weekbecame the latest victim of the turmoil in Brasilia overgovernment economic policy.    Sayad disagreed with Finance Minister Dilson Funaro, themost important minister for economic affairs, on a range ofpolicy issues and submitted his resignation. Reuter&#3;